<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[738,1333,494,922]" lastBlockId="4.[120,1331,926,2260]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="FitzGibbon" authorityYear="1966" box="[741,1025,692,725]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Salpingotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="michaelis">Salpingotus michaelis</taxonomicName>
is in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pavlinov" authorityYear="1980" box="[741,917,731,764]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Salpingotulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Salpingotulus</taxonomicName>
. It is considered by some authors to be in a separate genus, but its position on the phylogenetic tree constructed with use of morphological characteristics place it in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vinogradov" authorityYear="1922" box="[1038,1186,889,922]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Salpingotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Salpingotus</taxonomicName>
, being sister group of Anguistodontus. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[126,692,970,999]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1" type="multiple">
